# Goâ€‘Cordance

Goâ€‘Cordance is a lightweight 3D engine prototype written in Go.  
It explores how far Go can be pushed for realâ€‘time graphics, physics, and entityâ€‘componentâ€‘system (ECS) style architecture. The project is experimental but already demonstrates meshes, materials, cameras, physics, and shaderâ€‘based rendering.

---

## âœ¨ Features

- **Entityâ€“Componentâ€“System (ECS) architecture**
  - Entities composed of modular components (Mesh, Material, Camera, etc.)
  - Systems update and render components independently

- **Rendering**
  - OpenGL pipeline with GLSL shaders
  - Mesh support (including sphere meshes with normals)
  - Material properties (ambient, diffuse, specular, shininess)
  - Debug overlays (wireframe colliders, bounding boxes)

- **Physics**
  - Basic collision detection and rigid body updates
  - Collider visualization integrated into the render loop

- **Camera**
  - Minimal Camera component and CameraSystem
  - View/projection matrix handling
  - Lighting uniforms passed through camera system

- **Debugging**
  - Toggleable debug rendering system
  - Separate shader for collider visualization
  - Empirical validation of material/shader differences

- **Textures**
  - Simple texture system introduced

- **Mesh Loader**
  - A simple MeshLoader was introduced to load .obj files

