## ğŸš€ Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Go 1.21+ (modules enabled)
- OpenGL drivers (tested with modern desktop GPUs)
- `glfw` and `go-gl` bindings (installed via `go get`)

### Build & Run
```bash
git clone https://github.com/benes83-fra/Go-Cordance.git
cd Go-Cordance/cmd/game
go run .

This will launch the demo scene with camera, meshes, and physics enabled.

The camera can be controled WASD + Mouse,
F1 toggles/untoggles Collsion Debugging
F2 toggles/untoggles Lighting Debuggen

The Lightsource rotation can be stopped/started with SPACE
and the arrow keys allow to move the the light independently of the gizmo


